config BR2_PACKAGE_GT_BE98_RC
	bool "gt-be98-rc (rc, from source)"
	select BR2_PACKAGE_GT_BE98_LIBSHARED
	select BR2_PACKAGE_GT_BE98_NVRAM
	help
	  Builds the asuswrt-merlin router init/service engine (rc) FROM
	  SOURCE via the merlin SDK build-glue (SRCBASE/HND_SRC + the
	  fully-expanded -DGTBE98 CFLAGS) with
	  ASUSWRT_BRCM_SDK_VERSION=WIFI7_SDK_20231126 (selects the GT-BE98
	  _be prebuild .o variant). The 108 open .c are compiled and linked
	  against: the from-source libshared (gt-be98-libshared), the
	  from-source/clean-room libnvram (gt-be98-nvram), and the
	  irreducible-core vendor libs (wpa_client/ethctl/gen_util/sys_util/
	  wlcsm/bcm_flashutil/bcm_util/bcm_boardctl/bcm/wlc_nt_client/disk +
	  json-c/sqlite/openssl) which are PINNED graft inputs sourced from
	  the SDK build tree.

	  Result: ELF32 ARM EABI5 executable, full DT_NEEDED closure (36
	  libs) resolves; rc verbs (start_*/stop_*/notify_rc/sync_boot_state)
	  present. This is the from-source rc that unblocks the OpenRC
	  rc-demotion (reboot-site patches). Requires the firmware tree at
	  $(BR2_EXTERNAL)/../gt-be98-firmware. Not wired into the production
	  image.
